  "description": [
    "24 Pages Coday M MMWM\u00c6 WANT 24 Pa fits Coday VOLUME LXXV MONTGOMERY ALABAMA SUNDAY APRIL 17 1904 r NUMBER 108 EVERY MAN WAS A HERO Greatest Bravery Shown on Missouri SPLENDID WORKOFCOWLES Saved Lives of Several of the Crew Seamen McDade and Wells by Extra ordinary Nerve and ClearHeaded ness Prevented Complete De struction of the Battleship Pensacola April 1Every officer and man on the Missouri is a hero and that too under circumstances which would try the souls of the braveston earth said an officer of high rank here today who is thoroughly familiar with the circum stances of the explosion and the conduct of the officers and men during the fifteen minutes that the fire raged In the turret and handling room Little additional light is thrown on the cause of the explosion all agreeing that the rapid fire was the primary cause The day brought forth many incidents of heroism displayed by officers and men Two of the men now in the hospital will receive consideration from the Navy De partment for valiant service The two men arc Seamen McDade and Welles While many others of the crew assisted in saving the ship from total destruction"
